    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LAWRENCE, Kansas \u2013\nJunior\nTre Broussard\ncontinued a hot streak at the plate with three extra-base hits as Houston Baseball fell to Kansas in a 9-8 heartbreaker on Saturday at Hoglund Ballpark.\nTyler Bryan\n(1-2) gave up the walk-off single to take the loss on the mound for Houston (12-10, 1-4 Big 12). Kannon Carr (2-0) picked up the win despite allowing two runs on two hits in his 1.0 inning on the mound for Kansas (14-8, 3-2 Big 12).\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nTre Broussard\n: 4-5, HR, 2 2B, 3 RBI, 2 R\nRiley Jackson\n: 1-5, HR, 2 RBI, R\nEaston Winfield\n: 1-4, HR, RBI, R, BB\nTyler Cox\n: 2-4, 2 R\nNOTABLES\nHouston hit three homers in a game for the fifth time this season.\nBroussard earned his 20\nth\ncareer multi-RBI game with three in the game.\nThe Cougars reached double-digit hits for the 10\nth\ntime this season with 11 in the game.\nBroussard tallied four hits in a game for the second time in his career and hit his 10\nth\ncareer homer.\nBroussard has posted multiple hits in four straight games. Over the last four games, he has 10 hits for a .556 average (10-for-18).\nGAME SUMMARY\nKansas struck first with a solo homer in the bottom of the opening frame, but Houston tied it as Broussard doubled home Helton in the third.\nThe Jayhawks reclaimed the lead with a three-run homer from Tyson Owens in the fourth, his first of two on the day. The Cougars answered quickly with four runs in the fifth to earn their first lead of the game. Redshirt sophomore\nXavier Perez\nstarted the scoring with a single that also forced an error to drive home two before junior\nRiley Jackson\ncrushed a two-run homer to left to put Houston up 5-4.\nJunior\nEaston Winfield\nextended Houston's lead with his first homer of the season in the eighth, but Kansas fought back in the bottom of the frame. Owens hit his second homer of the game, a grand slam that put the Jayhawks up 8-6 going into the final inning.\nBroussard came through for the Cougars in the team's final at-bat, hitting a two-run homer that evened the score at 8-8. In the bottom of the ninth, Owens claimed the 9-8 win for Kansas with a walk-off single to clinch the series for the Jayhawks.\nUP NEXT\nHouston wraps up the three-game series against Kansas at noon Sunday.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013",
